Artist: After designs by François Perrier (French, Saint-Jean-du-Losne/Mâcon 1584–1650 Paris)
Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History: French Decorative Arts during the Reign of Louis XIV (1654–1715)
Description: This print is bound in Volume III of Oeuvres.  Jombert published his collection of Le Pautre in 1751. Volume III contains "desseins d'orfeverie, serrurerie, etc.;" This print is part of a series of thirteen plates depicting figure studies, comprising a book of portraiture dedicated to the Duke of Enghien.
